\title{Fixpoint}

\p{A \em{fixpoint} (or \em{fixed point}) of a function #{f: S \to S} is an element #{x \in S} such that applying the function #{f} to #{x} returns #{x} itself. In other words, #{x} is a fixpoint of #{f} if the following condition holds: [(1)](baanen-bentkamp-blanchette-holzl-limperg-hitchhikers-2024)}
##{
  f(x) = x
}
\p{This means that when you input #{x} into the function #{f}, the output is the same as the input.}